From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] clk: sunxi-ng: suniv: reparent VE clock to PLL_VE with
 rate propagation

The suniv CCU models the VE gate as a child of pll-audio, with a TODO
noting it should most likely be pll-ve.  On F1C200s hardware the video
engine demonstrably follows PLL_VE's rate, so make pll-ve the parent.

Also set CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT: the VE clock is a plain gate (no
divider, F1C200s user manual 3.2.5.26), so without rate propagation a
clk_set_rate() from the VE driver is absorbed by the gate and the
engine stays at PLL_VE's power-on default of 210 MHz (24 MHz * 35 / 4)
- which is exactly the rate previously measured while the driver was
requesting 297 MHz.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-suniv-f1c100s.c | 13 ++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-suniv-f1c100s.c
+++ b/drivers/clk/sunxi-ng/ccu-suniv-f1c100s.c
@@ -308,10 +308,15 @@
 				       0x120, 0, 4, 8, 3, BIT(15), 0);
 
 /*
- * TODO: BSP says the parent is pll-audio, however common sense and experience
- * told us it should be pll-ve. pll-ve is totally not used in BSP code.
+ * The BSP structures name pll-audio here, but on real F1C100s/F1C200s
+ * hardware the video engine demonstrably runs at PLL_VE's rate, so the
+ * gate feeds from PLL_VE.  CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT lets the VE driver's
+ * clk_set_rate() propagate through the gate to the PLL; without it the
+ * engine is stuck at PLL_VE's power-on default (24 MHz * 35 / 4 =
+ * 210 MHz) no matter what rate is requested.
  */
-static SUNXI_CCU_GATE(ve_clk, "ve", "pll-audio", 0x13c, BIT(31), 0);
+static SUNXI_CCU_GATE(ve_clk, "ve", "pll-ve", 0x13c, BIT(31),
+		      CLK_SET_RATE_PARENT);
 
 static SUNXI_CCU_GATE(codec_clk, "codec", "pll-audio", 0x140, BIT(31), 0);
 
